Two Nollywood stars Toyin Abraham and Odunlade Adekola couldn’t hide their joy as the Chief Executive Officer of Revolution Plus, Bamidele Onalaja turned 58. Abraham and Adekola took to their individual social media pages to felicitate Onalaja, who used the opportunity to give back to over 100 widows in different parts of Lagos. Abraham wrote, “Happy birthday popsy, Bamidele Onalaja oko Aunty Tolu mi. God bless your new age sir and thanks for always looking out for everyone around you, love you so much, sir.”   Seun Kuti & Egypt 80 band partner Roland corporation     How I was able to avoid sex for role, by Nnaji Charity     BON unveils logo for The Nigerian broadcasting Award   On his part, Adekola referred to the realtor as a great man and philanthropist per excellence. “Happy birthday to the great man. Our wonderful number one philanthropist per excellence. God will bless your new age baba.” On Monday, May 23, 2022, Onalaja under the Chris Bamidele Onalaja Foundation put smiles on the faces of 100 widows and women in celebration of his birthday. At the Ikeja office of Revolution Plus group, Onalaja gave out 40 grinding machines to 40 widows. “Grand finale of the birthday celebration today of as we empower all these widows today giving them grinding machines, sewing machines, cash gifts to start their soap making business,” Onalaja and his wife, Tolulope said in a brief chat. The Nation also gathered that Onalaja also gave out cash gifts of N50,000 each to 40 widows to start making soaps after undergoing a training session earlier in the year. The Onalaja couple also said the decision to empower the widows stems from the six-point focus of the foundation which includes children, education, mental health, economic empowerment, and others.